Sarah got stuck in a blizzard last night on her way back up to the U.P.  She had to stay the night at a hotel in Gaylord.  Now today the 2 major highways in the U.P. are closed which makes it a huge pain in the ass for her to get back home.  It pisses me off that they can't keep the 2 major highways clear up there.  If you dont have a 4 wheel drive you are basically screwed.  I just can't wait for it to be Spring of 09 so we will both be graduated and there will be no more trips to and from the U.P.  She is amazing and I hate worrying about her on those long trips.  Anyways, I just thought I would vent because I think the U.P. should be used to getting blizzard by now and have a way to fix it.  

Also, I hate snow days in college.  Everyone likes them the day of, but then professors assume that you will still work on your homework all day......riiiiiiiiight.  So now I'm even farther behind on my readings.  Hurray for getting in over my head!

Thats all for now.

So I had my first interview today at Wolverine Human Services in Vassar.  The pioneer work and learn center is a boot camp for juvenile delinquints.  Its military like, with uniforms and marching.  

I will be starting out as a Buck Sergant.  This is as close to the military that I will ever get probably lol.  The kids will most likely be little dicks but oh well.  I will be starting at around $8.65/hr I believe.  If I have 60 credits it will be more but I don't think I have that many yet.  I have to shave off my chin fuzz :(

I have a bunch of paper work to do this weekend. 

Talk to ya all later

TP

Well everyone, I'm back online after a couple days of no cable internet.  It was hard for all of us but luckily we made it.  I am officially moved into the house and and every thing is going pretty good.  Now that we have cable I can pretty much continue my old ruetine.  The only thing thats different is that I'm going to the YMCA every day now and eating healthy.  I figured this would be the perfect time to change my life around for the better.  I must say it is a hell of a lot easier to eat healthy when you are buying your own food.  I have a limited cash flow being that I am unemployed so I have to try to save money.  This means there won't be fast food purchases.  Because the 5 bucks I would spend at a fast food place could by a loaf of bread and lunch meat which would last a lot longer.  The YMCA in owosso doesn't have a pool but it does have a steam room in sauna.  I enjoy sitting in these rooms and cleaning out the pores.  I'm hoping to be "in shape" by next fall.  For all you skinny people out there it might seem like a long time considering I'm working out daily and eating right but its really hard to lose large amounts of weight.  AFter all I'm not talking about 5-10 vanity pounds.  Well I'm sure I've bored you all long enough so I'm gonna get ready to go to the Y.  See ya soon!

~Tybob

Last night the crew went to the machine shop and watched a couple bands that we knew.  It was pretty sweet, Second System was awesome.  It was too crazy for me seeing Myron Leslie there.  Frank went over and talked to him but I never got around to it.  I guess he was pretty wasted.  The fun came after we left the shop and went over to Brett's house because he had a keg and both bands we were watching at the machine shop came over.  They played a little bit on the equipment Brett has for Broken Down.  The whole experience was pretty trippy but it was very fun.  Tony also came which was cool because he had to work this morning early and he still came out and had a few brewskies.  I didn't make it to bed until about 4 this morning but I'm still feeling pretty good.  My morning afters are usually a nice relaxed feeling.  Well I had a bitchin time last night and I thought I would share it with you fine folks.

~TP

Well the other day when I was out in my car I decided to roll down the windows to clean them off a little bit.  The Problem is that when I went to roll the window back up it wouldn't go.  It was stuck in the completely as far down as it gets position.  So we took my car to Oliver's Garage and had him check it out.  He just called me and told me that it needs a new window motor.  He mentioned that it is gonna be $150 for parts and labor.  The only thing worse than things breaking on your car is things breaking on your car right before you are trying to sell it.  Obviously I can't sell it if the window is stuck in the down position.  I might be able to get away with something like that in the summer time but definately not when its friggin 20 friggin degrees out.  The cool thing is that I can still drive the Caprice.  That car has 265K miles on it and it still has minimal problems **knock on wood**.  I will just drive that for now until I get the Grand Prix fixed.  There are things to be happy about though.  One thing is the fact that it is Friday.  I'm sure you all know what goes down on Fridays.  The Crew will make a move while we bust a groove while we in the club, show us some love.  Either that or we will just get crunked at someones house.  It will probably be that one.  New update on the crew website...all pictures are being put on a separate website to save bandwidth.  I will just put a link to the pictures on Crew website.  This will also allow me to have a lot more pictures for you all to view.  I am in the process of archiving all the old photoes I have and after that I will put up a new page for new photos.  Well I'm gonna hop in the shower so I'll talk to ya later.

~Tieler Pain

Well today is Tuesday and its friggin rainin.  I was supposed to go snowmobiling this weekend for a guys weekend but its not lookin good at all.  The thing I hate the most is the solid ice, the reason is because yesterday when I was walking out to my car I fell on my azz and my OS concepts book fell in the mud.  If my dirty wet pants weren't enough, I had to damage the $80 book.  I can't believe this is the 6th week of school already.  With Baker only having 10 weeks of class, that means I'm starting to wind down the semester.  I think I have A's in both Math and English and a B+ in OS concepts.  Yesterday was valentines day and Jessie was my valentine :).  I hung out with Frank and Jessie the first have of the day and later on Me, Landon, and my parents went to the Pistons game and had lower lvl seats, it was very nice.  The pistons blew out the bucks by over 20 points and Darko had a season high.  It was a good game to go to.  The coolest part is they were 60 dollar seats and we got them from a season-ticket holder for free.  Well that, and gettin all buzzed up on the way down there.  Today I have Enlgish from 2-3:50 which sucks because I hate the class and I dont know whats due today.  I need to get my teeth all sparkling clean so I'll check back in with you fine folks later.

~Tyrell Baynes

Well lahhdie frickin dah!!  Guess who's back?  Thats right, its Capital T to the Y live and in living color.  A nice pasty white color.  Anyways, today was great because I dropped my Networking Essentials class and it will not effect my GPA.  Also I talked with the head of the Education department and she gave me some materials to look over.  Because if you haven't heard the latest headlines, TPayne is gonna be a teacher...(This is the part wear you roll on the ground laughing uncontrolably).  What made Tyler decide to be a teacher you may ask?  Short answer: Its in the blood.  I don't want to ramble on to much about me going into Teaching (going to Major in Computer Science and Minor in History).  There is nothing easy about the teaching profession but I was attracted by the vacation time.  So whats new with me...haven't updated this shiznizzle in awhile.  Oh yeah, I know what to talk about, The STUPID BOWL.  I mean Super Bowl.  Is anyone having a bowl party?  IF you are, don't be too shy to send an invite over this way.  I watched a few episodes of Celebrity Fit Club and got attached.  Being a fat person myself, I instantly liked seeing famous people struggle with trying to lose weight.  I am currently trying to lose weight as well but I swear my frickin metabolism is as slow as a snail.  Its not all genetics fault, I need to get out and exercise more.  I could probably have a six pack in a week if I spent the amount of time in the gym that I spend playing EQ2 or messing around on the computer.  One thing that is good to have though is a workout partner, its always funner that way.  If you are intersted post on here.  I currently have a YMCA membership in saginaw but I will be transferring it to Owosso when I move out that way.  Well I have an Intermediate Algebra Class from 6-9:40 so I guess I'll be going now.  Talk to you all sooner or later.  Hopefully sooner.

~T.J.P

Well I'm sure you all noticed livejournals little problem over the weekend.  May I be one of the firsts to say they did an excellent job in putting their full efforts in restoring everyone's data. I did go with Frank to Saginaw and thats about it.  People must be tired of me again.  Oh well.  I got my homework done for Monday so Monday should be stress free for me yippee. So yeah, my fat ass started my diet/exercise program yesterday.  My diet isn't really conventional, its mainly dividing everything I used to eat in half.  The exercise part is the bitch of it.  The ironic thing is I actually like the feeling I get after the work out but while I'm doing the work out I feel dead.  Anyways, I dont know how much you all know about Pilates but like 2 years ago I got my mom a pilates dvd (covered in dust by now).  So I thought i would bust it out.  I tell you what, ladies and gents, this shit is rough, and I'm the exercise tape master.  Richard Simmons, Tae-bo, Step Block...that stuff all seems like a piece of cake after pilates.  Ya see, Pilates concentrates on having your "core" tight during every exercise you do.  Your core is basically your abs and we all know, well maybe not all of us, but most of us know the ab pain after a long ab workout.  So with all that said, do I have any volunteers to be a Pilates partner.  Actually, nevermind, I'm not sure I want anyone watching me try to put my legs straight up in the air and touch them with my hands.

My first week of school went suprisingly well.  Actually, I have no complaints.  My biggest suprise was my math class.  Math class sucks, we all know that.  But this teacher seems pretty good, by good I mean she gets down on the teaching thing and she does it well.  Also, we all know that Math classes come with lots of homework.  Not with her, or at least it dont seem like it.  As for my other classes, my English class is pretty good, I mean my teacher is a ding bat but the actual class don't seem that hard.  And for my CIS (Computer Information Systems) classes, they look to be difficult but they also seem to be very informational and good for my career future.  Plus its a bonus to enjoy learning.

I have something to bitch about now.  I went to the Genesee Valley Mall yesterday in between classes and I got some Subway (goes good with the whole diet thing).  Now I'm not sure if the mall's prices are jacked up or subway in general raised their prices but for a 12" meal it was $8.50.  So I was like, ok, I'll pay it today and just pack a lunch from now on, I wasn't too pissed.  But right before I left I went for a refill on my diet pepsi and the BITCH behind the counter was like "you know its 50 cents for a refill".  And I was all like, "Are you serious?" and she said, "read the sign".  Sure as shit there was a sign on the pop machine, 50 cent refills.  That just chapped my ass because I know they just raped me to begin with on the price, now they want another 50 cents for a 10 cent refill (If you were wondering, 20 oz cups cost 10 cents to fill with fountain machines).  Well I think I'm done bitching for now, but I'm gonna put it on you now, I want to hear what you have to bitch about.  Leave a comment with one of your complaints, tell your friends about it.  I want to get lots of complaints on here.

T-Bag Out

Well hello faithful followers of Burt legend.  Just kidding.  Its been awhile I know but I'm starting to not be so apathetic lately.  Started school this week and its just some good clean fun.  My CIS classes seem like they will be the most informational and helpful toward my degree.  And since its a class for a dorky degree there aren't any hot chicks that distract me.  Thats the one bad thing about going into computer science, 90 percent of the people in the program are dudes, and the other 10 percent look like dudes.  Just kidding, they aren't all that bad.  The best program for picking up chicks would be the nursing program, which I heard Jason Jones is in, lucky bastard.  Anyways, here's how my schedule looks (as if any of you actually cared).  Monday- Operating Systems Concepts (6:00-9:40 P.M.) ; Tuesday- Composition II (2:00-3:50) and Essentials of Networking (6:00-9:40 P.M.) ; Wednesday - NO CLASS :) ; Thursday- Composition II (2:00-3:50) and Intermediate Algebra (6:00-9:40 P.M.).  That raps up my class schedule.  I bet by now you are wondering, he takes pretty much all night classes so he must have a job.  Well you would be right if I wouldn't have gotten laid off last month.  Fortunately I am collecting unemployment which isn't bad.  I don't make as good of money but considering I dont work for it, its pretty nice.  So basically I sleep in late and go to class late.  My mom calls me a hampster.  Anyways, I'll update this thing later, I gotta hop in the shower and get ready for class.

C-Ya L8R Chillins
~T-Bag
